            <!-- Rich Text Body -->
            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'zh'">
                <h2>1. 视觉钩子：前三秒定生死</h2>
<p>在 Meta（Facebook/Instagram）的信息流中，用户滑过一条动态的平均时间不足 <strong>1.5秒</strong>。<br />
如果你的素材不能在这个极短的时间内抓住眼球，再好的产品也会被淹没。</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>高对比度色彩</strong>：使用与 Facebook 蓝色主色调形成反差的暖色（如橙色、黄色）来吸引注意力。</li>
<li><strong>直击痛点</strong>：视频的开场不要放 Logo，而是直接抛出用户面临的问题，或者展示震撼的使用效果。</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. 避免素材疲劳的轮换策略</h2>
<p>即使是爆款素材，在连续跑了 2-3 周后，也会不可避免地遭遇<strong>素材疲劳（Ad Fatigue）</strong>，导致 CPA（获客成本）飙升。</p>
<h3>应对方法：</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>微调迭代</strong>：保留核心视频内容，仅更换视频的前 3 秒 Hook、背景音乐或是封面图。</li>
<li><strong>格式多样化</strong>：不要只投单视频。将表现好的视频截图，配上卖点文案，制作成轮播图（Carousel）或单图广告，覆盖不同偏好的受众。</li>
</ol>
<h2>3. 互动型广告的崛起</h2>
<p>如今的消费者越来越抵触生硬的推销。<br />
尝试在你的广告中加入互动元素：<br />
- <strong>投票贴</strong>：让用户在两个产品中做出选择。<br />
- <strong>AR 试穿/试用</strong>：利用 Meta 的 Spark AR 技术，让用户在广告中直接体验产品。<br />
只有让用户参与进来，才能建立更深的情感连接，从而推动最终的转化。</p>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'en'" x-cloak>
                <h2>1. Visual Hooks: The First 3 Seconds Decide Your Fate</h2>
<p>In the Meta (Facebook/Instagram) news feed, the average time a user spends scrolling past a post is less than <strong>1.5 seconds</strong>.<br />
If your creative cannot grab attention in this extremely short window, even the best product will go unnoticed.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>High-Contrast Colors</strong>: Use warm colors (like orange or yellow) that contrast with Facebook's primary blue to draw the eye.</li>
<li><strong>Directly Address Pain Points</strong>: Don't start your video with a logo. Immediately present a problem the user faces or show a stunning visual of the product's effect.</li>
</ul>
<h2>2. Rotation Strategies to Avoid Ad Fatigue</h2>
<p>Even winning creatives will inevitably suffer from <strong>Ad Fatigue</strong> after running for 2-3 weeks, causing CPAs (Cost Per Acquisition) to skyrocket.</p>
<h3>Countermeasures:</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Micro-Iterations</strong>: Keep the core video content, but swap out the first 3-second hook, background music, or thumbnail.</li>
<li><strong>Format Diversification</strong>: Don't rely solely on single videos. Take screenshots of high-performing videos, add selling point copy, and turn them into Carousel or Single Image ads to reach audiences with different preferences.</li>
</ol>
<h2>3. The Rise of Interactive Ads</h2>
<p>Today's consumers are increasingly resistant to hard selling.<br />
Try incorporating interactive elements into your ads:<br />
- <strong>Polls</strong>: Ask users to choose between two products.<br />
- <strong>AR Try-ons</strong>: Utilize Meta's Spark AR technology to let users experience the product directly within the ad.<br />
Only by engaging the user can you build a deeper emotional connection, which ultimately drives conversion.</p>
